@startuml akdb-deployment
title ArchitecturalKnowledgeDB - Deployment Options
node "Developer workstation" {
 artifact "akdb CLI / MCP / API" as App1
 database "SQLite file\n(default, local)" as SQLite
 App1 --> SQLite
}
node "Container / shared environment" {
 artifact "AKDB application container" as App2
 database "PostgreSQL 16" as PG
 App2 --> PG : AKDB_DB_URL
}
cloud "Optional semantic service" as Vector
folder "Read-only registered repositories" as Repos
folder "Versioned SAD/UML projections" as Projection
App1 --> Repos : scan
App2 --> Repos : mounted read-only
App1 --> Projection : export
App2 --> Projection : export
App1 --> Vector : optional
App2 --> Vector : optional
note bottom
SQLite and PostgreSQL are alternatives, not synchronized replicas.
Backups and lifecycle follow the selected backend's operations guide.
end note
@enduml
